With the global increase of the elderly population, the improvement of the 
treatment for various aging-related diseases and the extension of a healthy 
lifespan have become some of the most important current medical issues. In order 
to understand the developmental mechanisms of aging and aging-related disorders, 
animal models are essential to conduct relevant studies. Among them, mice have 
become one of the most prevalently used model animals for aging-related studies 
